BongoDB README

Welcome to BongoDB!

COMPONENTS

  bongod - The database server.
  bongos - Sharding router.
  bongo  - The database shell (uses interactive javascript).

UTILITIES

  bongodump         - Create a binary dump of the contents of a database.
  bongorestore      - Restore data from the output created by bongodump.
  bongoexport       - Export the contents of a collection to JSON or CSV.
  bongoimport       - Import data from JSON, CSV or TSV.
  bongofiles        - Put, get and delete files from GridFS.
  bongostat         - Show the status of a running bongod/bongos.
  bsondump          - Convert BSON files into human-readable formats.
  bongooplog        - Poll the oplog and apply to a local server.
  bongoreplay       - Traffic capture and replay tool.
  bongotop          - Track time spent reading and writing data.

BUILDING

  See docs/building.md.

RUNNING

  For command line options invoke:

    $ ./bongod --help

  To run a single server database:

    $ sudo mkdir -p /data/db
    $ ./bongod
    $
    $ # The bongo javascript shell connects to localhost and test database by default:
    $ ./bongo
    > help

DRIVERS

  Client drivers for most programming languages are available at
  https://docs.bongodb.com/manual/applications/drivers/. Use the shell
  ("bongo") for administrative tasks.

BUG REPORTS

  See https://github.com/bongodb/bongo/wiki/Submit-Bug-Reports.

PACKAGING

  Packages are created dynamically by the package.py script located in the
  buildscripts directory. This will generate RPM and Debian packages.

